text: Chernenko (; ), is a surname of Ukrainian origin. Notable persons with the surname include: * Konstantin Chernenko (1911–1985), leader of Soviet Union from 1984 to 1985 * Anna Chernenko (1913–2010), wife of Konstantin Chernenko * Albert Chernenko (1935–2009), Russian philosopher and son of Konstantin Chernenko * Elena Chernenko, minister of finance of Pridestrovian Moldavian Republic * Anastasiya Chernenko (born 1990), Ukrainian triathlete * Yevhen Chernenko (1934-2007), Ukrainian archaeologist == See also == * Cerna (surname) * Chernyaev Category:Ukrainian-language surnames
title: Chernenko (surname)
